p.-text Use progress to display the status of a task or process.

h2 Examples
p.-text
  | To render a progress element, use the tag <code>&lt;chi-progress&gt;</code>.
  | Set the <code>value</code> attribute to the amount of work completed. The default state is <code>success</code>.

h3 Base
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .a-label 0%
    chi-progress(value='0')
    .a-label 50%
    chi-progress(value='50')
    .a-label 100%
    chi-progress(value='100')
  :code(lang="html")
    <!-- 0% -->
    <div class="a-label">0%</div>
    <chi-progress value="0"></chi-progress>
    <!-- 50% -->
    <div class="a-label">50%</div>
    <chi-progress value="50"></chi-progress>
    <!-- 100% -->
    <div class="a-label">100%</div>
    <chi-progress value="100"></chi-progress>

h3 States
p.-text
  | To indicate a progress state, set the attribute <code>state</code> value to <code>info</code>, <code>warning</code>, <code>danger</code>, or <code>success</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .a-label Danger
    chi-progress(value='75', state='danger')
    .a-label Info
    chi-progress(value='75', state='info')
    .a-label Warning
    chi-progress(value='75', state='warning')
    .a-label Success
    chi-progress(value='75', state='success')
  :code(lang="html")
    <!-- Danger -->
    <div class="a-label">Danger</div>
    <chi-progress value="75" state="danger"></chi-progress>
    <!-- Info -->
    <div class="a-label">Info</div>
    <chi-progress value="75" state="info"></chi-progress>
    <!-- Warning -->
    <div class="a-label">Warning</div>
    <chi-progress value="75" state="warning"></chi-progress>
    <!-- Success -->
    <div class="a-label">Success</div>
    <chi-progress value="75" state="success"></chi-progress>

